WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:24.720
Land of Gold by Claire Craig

00:24.720 --> 00:36.720
Copyright 2007, Newhouse and International Language Teaching Services, PTY Ltd.

00:36.720 --> 00:47.720
Track 3. I sit beside the pyramid. My feet are hot. Mr. Johnson is speaking about King Cheops and his pyramid.

00:47.720 --> 00:49.720
I shut my eyes.

00:49.720 --> 00:55.720
Maddy says Kate in my ear. Open your eyes.

00:55.720 --> 00:59.720
No, I say. I'm sleeping.

00:59.720 --> 01:05.720
Maddy says Kate again. I open one eye.

01:05.720 --> 01:10.720
A man is looking at us, she says.

01:10.720 --> 01:13.720
Who? I ask.

01:13.720 --> 01:20.720
That man over there, she says. The man in the black suit.

01:20.720 --> 01:29.720
I see the man. He is looking at us. He is standing beside the pyramid.

01:29.720 --> 01:35.720
He's a bad man, says Kate. I know it.

01:35.720 --> 01:43.720
Kate wants to be a detective. She reads detective books. She writes detective stories.

01:43.720 --> 01:49.720
In her stories, the bad men are always in black suits.

01:49.720 --> 01:56.720
No, he isn't, I say. He's looking at the pyramids.

01:56.720 --> 02:03.720
I am hot. I want to be in our hotel. I want to sleep.

02:03.720 --> 02:09.720
But, says Kate. Mr. Johnson looks at her.

02:09.720 --> 02:11.720
What is it, Kate?

02:11.720 --> 02:20.720
Kate doesn't answer. She's writing stories in her head again, says Paul Hand.

02:20.720 --> 02:23.720
Mr. Johnson smiles at Kate.

02:23.720 --> 02:30.720
You and your stories, he says. Kate's face is red.

02:30.720 --> 02:40.720
Okay, he says. The bus is going to take us to the hotel now.

02:40.720 --> 02:46.720
Track four. I look at Kate and say, what?

02:46.720 --> 02:51.720
This is not my bag, she says again.

02:51.720 --> 02:57.720
It is your bag, I say. No, it's not, she says.

02:57.720 --> 03:08.720
It is a brown bag, but it's new. My bag is old. Look, what's this?

03:08.720 --> 03:16.720
Kate is looking inside the bag. I go to the table. I look inside the bag too.

03:16.720 --> 03:23.720
I see a small yellow statue. It shines like the sun.

03:24.720 --> 03:29.720
Kate takes it out of the bag and puts it on the table.

03:29.720 --> 03:34.720
It is a statue of an Egyptian woman.

03:34.720 --> 03:42.720
I think she's an Egyptian queen, says Kate. Look at her clothes.

03:42.720 --> 03:50.720
Is it a gold statue? I ask. I don't know, says Kate.

03:50.720 --> 03:57.720
She picks up the statue again. It's heavy, she says, and puts it down again.

03:57.720 --> 04:08.720
I pick it up. It is heavy, I say. Gold is heavy.

04:08.720 --> 04:11.720
Track five.

04:11.720 --> 04:17.720
Okay, says Mr. Johnson. Get your bags and come with me.

04:17.720 --> 04:22.720
The hotel is near here. We're going to walk to it.

04:22.720 --> 04:28.720
We get off the train. We walk through the streets of Aswan.

04:28.720 --> 04:32.720
Lots of people are in the streets and in the shops.

04:32.720 --> 04:39.720
You can buy clothes and gold and silver in the shops, says Mr. Johnson.

04:39.720 --> 04:49.720
And today is Market Day. The market has stalls with spices, rugs, food and coffee.

04:49.720 --> 04:55.720
The statue, Kate, I say to her. Are we going to tell Mr. Johnson?

04:55.720 --> 05:01.720
Yes, at the hotel, says Kate. We can tell him there.

05:02.720 --> 05:11.720
Okay, I say. We walk past the shops and stalls. I can smell the spices.

05:11.720 --> 05:17.720
I can smell coffee and food. I like the red and yellow rugs.

05:17.720 --> 05:23.720
Can we stop, please, Mr. Johnson? Says Peter Small.

05:23.720 --> 05:28.720
Paul Hand is taking photos of the things in the market.

05:28.720 --> 05:32.720
Mr. Johnson looks at us. Okay.

05:32.720 --> 05:38.720
He says and smiles. Kate and I look at a shop with clothes.

05:38.720 --> 05:50.720
We look at a stool with bags of spices. We go into a shop with silver and gold.

05:50.720 --> 05:55.720
Track six. Mr. Johnson is looking at us.

05:55.720 --> 06:05.720
Your bag is missing. He says to Kate. Yes, she says. But it's not my bag.

06:05.720 --> 06:14.720
And this bag has a missing statue in it? Says Mr. Johnson. Yes, we say.

06:14.720 --> 06:19.720
And the police are looking for this man, says Kate.

06:19.720 --> 06:23.720
She gives Mr. Johnson the photo of the man in black.

06:23.720 --> 06:31.720
Look, do you see? He's taking my bag and he's putting his bag in its place.

06:31.720 --> 06:39.720
What? Says Mr. Johnson. He gives you his bag with a statue in it.

06:39.720 --> 06:45.720
Yes, he's hiding the statue, I say.

06:45.720 --> 06:51.720
The police aren't going to look for the statue in a school girl's bag, says Kate.

06:51.720 --> 06:55.720
It's a good place to hide a statue.

06:55.720 --> 07:01.720
And where is this statue now? Says Mr. Johnson.

07:01.720 --> 07:08.720
He has it again, says Kate. He's here in us one too.

07:08.720 --> 07:13.720
Mr. Johnson doesn't speak. Then he smiles.

07:13.720 --> 07:18.720
It's a good story, girls. He says.

07:18.720 --> 07:26.720
The gold statue of an Egyptian queen, a man in black, the police.

07:26.720 --> 07:30.720
It's a good detective story.

07:35.720 --> 07:41.720
Chapter 1, the man in black.

07:41.720 --> 07:45.720
This is a photo of Kate and me in Egypt.

07:45.720 --> 07:49.720
I'm Maddie. I'm in the red dress.

07:49.720 --> 07:54.720
I'm standing beside Mr. Johnson, our teacher.

07:54.720 --> 07:58.720
Kate is the girl with the brown bag.

07:58.720 --> 08:02.720
We are in Egypt with our class from school.

08:02.720 --> 08:05.720
We are standing beside a pyramid.

08:05.720 --> 08:09.720
A camel with a big nose is behind us.

08:09.720 --> 08:13.720
The camel wants to be in the photo.

08:13.720 --> 08:17.720
Smile, says Paul Hand.

08:17.720 --> 08:21.720
We smile and Paul takes the photo.

08:21.720 --> 08:27.720
We take photos of the pyramids too. They are big in the blue sky.

08:27.720 --> 08:33.720
The sun is hot in Egypt. My face and arms are red.

08:33.720 --> 08:39.720
I have a drink of water. I look at Kate. She is hot too.

08:39.720 --> 08:43.720
Mr. Johnson is speaking about the pyramid.

08:43.720 --> 08:50.720
This is the pyramid of King Chios, a pharaoh or king of Egypt.

08:50.720 --> 08:55.720
I sit beside the pyramid. My feet are hot.

08:55.720 --> 09:02.720
Mr. Johnson is speaking about King Chios and his pyramid. I shut my eyes.

09:02.720 --> 09:06.720
Maddie, says Kate in my ear.

09:06.720 --> 09:08.720
Open your eyes.

09:08.720 --> 09:12.720
No, I say. I'm sleeping.

09:12.720 --> 09:16.720
Maddie, says Kate again.

09:16.720 --> 09:18.720
I open one eye.

09:18.720 --> 09:23.720
A man is looking at us, she says.

09:23.720 --> 09:26.720
Who? I ask.

09:26.720 --> 09:30.720
That man over there, she says.

09:30.720 --> 09:34.720
The man in the black suit.

09:34.720 --> 09:42.720
I see the man. He is looking at us. He is standing beside the pyramid.

09:42.720 --> 09:48.720
He's a bad man, says Kate. I know it.

09:48.720 --> 09:53.720
Kate wants to be a detective. She reads detective books.

09:53.720 --> 09:56.720
She writes detective stories.

09:56.720 --> 10:02.720
In her stories, the bad men are always in black suits.

10:02.720 --> 10:09.720
No, he isn't, I say. He's looking at the pyramids.

10:09.720 --> 10:16.720
I am hot. I want to be in our hotel. I want to sleep.

10:16.720 --> 10:22.720
But, says Kate. Mr. Johnson looks at her.

10:22.720 --> 10:24.720
What is it, Kate?

10:24.720 --> 10:27.720
Kate doesn't answer.

10:27.720 --> 10:33.720
She's writing stories in her head again, says Paul Hand.

10:33.720 --> 10:36.720
Mr. Johnson smiles at Kate.

10:36.720 --> 10:40.720
You and your stories, he says.

10:40.720 --> 10:43.720
Kate's face is red.

10:43.720 --> 10:45.720
Okay, he says.

10:45.720 --> 10:50.720
The bus is going to take us to the hotel now.

10:50.720 --> 10:56.720
Paul Hand takes a photo of the bus. He is always taking photos.

10:56.720 --> 11:04.720
We get on the bus. I sit beside the window. Kate sits beside me.

11:04.720 --> 11:07.720
I look at the hot yellow land.

11:07.720 --> 11:14.720
Soon, the pyramids are behind us. They look small now.

11:14.720 --> 11:17.720
The bus stops at our hotel in Cairo.

11:17.720 --> 11:21.720
The afternoon sun is hot like the morning sun.

11:21.720 --> 11:25.720
Kate takes her bag and gets up.

11:25.720 --> 11:30.720
I look out of the window and I see the man in the black suit.

11:30.720 --> 11:37.720
He is standing across the street. A brown bag is on the ground beside him.

11:37.720 --> 11:41.720
He is looking at our bus.

11:42.720 --> 11:46.720
What's he doing here? I ask.

11:46.720 --> 11:49.720
Who, says Kate?

11:49.720 --> 11:54.720
Look, the man in black is across the street.

11:54.720 --> 11:56.720
She looks at him.

11:56.720 --> 12:01.720
Yes, what is he doing here? She says.

12:01.720 --> 12:05.720
I don't like that man.

12:05.720 --> 12:09.720
We get off the bus. I look across the street again.

12:09.720 --> 12:13.720
Now I can't see the man in black.

12:13.720 --> 12:18.720
I have one photo to take, says Paul Hand.

12:18.720 --> 12:26.720
I'm going to take a photo of the hotel. Kate, Maddie, can you stand there please?

12:26.720 --> 12:30.720
Kate puts her bag on the ground behind her.

12:30.720 --> 12:36.720
We stand in front of the hotel and smile. Paul takes the photo.

12:36.720 --> 12:42.720
Thanks, he says. Now I'm going to take these to the photo shop.

12:42.720 --> 12:49.720
It's four o'clock now. Dinner is at six o'clock, says Mr. Johnson.

12:49.720 --> 12:53.720
Yes, Mr. Johnson, we say.

12:53.720 --> 12:57.720
Kate takes her bag and we walk into the hotel.

12:57.720 --> 13:04.720
We go to our room and shut the door. The room is nice and cold.

13:04.720 --> 13:10.720
I sit on the bed and drink water. Kate puts her bag on the table.

13:10.720 --> 13:15.720
I'm tired. I lie down and go to sleep.

13:15.720 --> 13:19.720
I open my eyes. Kate is talking.

13:19.720 --> 13:25.720
Now, where is my book on Egypt? She is saying.

13:25.720 --> 13:31.720
It's in my bag. I want to read about the Temple of Ramesses, the Great.

13:31.720 --> 13:36.720
She opens the bag. We are going to go there tomorrow.

13:36.720 --> 13:43.720
It's in Abu symbol, near Azwan. The Temple of Ramesses, the Great, is...

13:43.720 --> 13:46.720
She stops speaking.

13:46.720 --> 13:53.720
Maddie, she says, this is not my bag.

13:53.720 --> 14:03.720
Chapter 2, the Egyptian Queen.

14:03.720 --> 14:12.720
I look at Kate and say, what? This is not my bag, she says again.

14:12.720 --> 14:19.720
It is your bag, I say. No, it's not, she says.

14:19.720 --> 14:30.720
It is a brown bag, but it's new. My bag is old. Look, what's this?

14:30.720 --> 14:38.720
Kate is looking inside the bag. I go to the table. I look inside the bag too.

14:38.720 --> 14:45.720
I see a small yellow statue. It shines like the sun.

14:45.720 --> 14:50.720
Kate takes it out of the bag and puts it on the table.

14:50.720 --> 14:55.720
It is a statue of an Egyptian woman.

14:55.720 --> 15:03.720
I think she's an Egyptian queen, says Kate. Look at her clothes.

15:03.720 --> 15:11.720
Is it a gold statue? I ask. I don't know, says Kate.

15:11.720 --> 15:19.720
She picks up the statue again. It's heavy, she says, and puts it down again.

15:19.720 --> 15:28.720
I pick it up. It is heavy, I say. Gold is heavy.

15:28.720 --> 15:32.720
Kate looks at the small pictures on the statue.

15:32.720 --> 15:37.720
These pictures are hieroglyphs, she says.

15:37.720 --> 15:45.720
My book on Egypt has a chapter on hieroglyphs. They are like words, they tell stories.

15:45.720 --> 15:54.720
What do these hieroglyphs say? I ask. I don't know, I can't read hieroglyphs.

15:54.720 --> 16:01.720
Kate says, my book is in my bag, and this isn't my bag.

16:01.720 --> 16:05.720
I'm going to tell Mr. Johnson about the statue, I say.

16:05.720 --> 16:13.720
No, says Kate. Don't tell Mr. Johnson. But knock, knock.

16:13.720 --> 16:20.720
We both jump and look at the door. Yes, says Kate. Who is it?

16:20.720 --> 16:29.720
It's Mr. Johnson. Come on you two. It's six o'clock. Dinner is on the table.

16:29.720 --> 16:35.720
Kate puts the statue inside the bag. She puts the bag under her bed.

16:35.720 --> 16:41.720
We're coming, Mr. Johnson. She says. She looks at me.

16:41.720 --> 16:50.720
It's okay, Maddie. Mr. Johnson has a book on hieroglyphs. I'm going to ask him for it.

16:50.720 --> 16:56.720
Do you think the name of the queen is in the hieroglyphs? I ask.

16:56.720 --> 17:03.720
Yes, she answers. And I'm a detective, she says, with a smile.

17:03.720 --> 17:08.720
A detective can find out the name of an Egyptian queen.

17:08.720 --> 17:12.720
She opens the door and walks out.

17:12.720 --> 17:17.720
The class is eating dinner. Mr. Johnson looks at us.

17:17.720 --> 17:22.720
You two are always late, he says.

17:22.720 --> 17:30.720
Kate smiles at him. It's Maddie, Mr. Johnson. She says. She is always late.

17:30.720 --> 17:36.720
She smiles at me. We sit beside Paul Hand and Peter Small.

17:36.720 --> 17:40.720
Mr. Johnson is speaking about the journey to Azwan.

17:40.720 --> 17:46.720
We have a big day tomorrow. We're going to Azwan by train.

17:46.720 --> 17:50.720
He says, it's a long journey.

17:50.720 --> 17:54.720
How long is the journey? Says Peter.

17:54.720 --> 17:57.720
It's about 12 hours.

17:57.720 --> 18:01.720
Says Mr. Johnson. He looks at Kate and me.

18:01.720 --> 18:05.720
Don't be late in the morning, you two.

18:05.720 --> 18:12.720
12 hours on a train? Kate says to me. What are we going to do?

18:12.720 --> 18:18.720
Look, girls. Says Paul Hand. I have the photos.

18:18.720 --> 18:21.720
He puts them on the table in front of us.

18:21.720 --> 18:25.720
These are the photos at the pyramids, he says.

18:25.720 --> 18:30.720
Look at the camel. He's eating your hat, Kate.

18:30.720 --> 18:37.720
We look at photos of the sky, the bus, the road, a camel, the hotel.

18:37.720 --> 18:43.720
Kate and me in front of the hotel. I look at that photo again.

18:43.720 --> 18:47.720
My face is hot. Kate, look at this.

18:47.720 --> 18:51.720
The photo of you and me in front of the hotel.

18:51.720 --> 18:58.720
Kate looks at it. In the photo, a man is behind Kate.

18:58.720 --> 19:05.720
He is picking up her bag. He is putting his bag on the ground.

19:05.720 --> 19:09.720
Kate's face is white. What is it?

19:09.720 --> 19:13.720
asks Paul. Don't you like the photo?

19:13.720 --> 19:17.720
No, I do. I do like this photo.

19:17.720 --> 19:23.720
Says Kate. Can I keep it, please, Paul? Yes, you can keep it.

19:23.720 --> 19:27.720
Says Paul. Thank you, says Kate.

19:27.720 --> 19:31.720
She looks at me. Come on.

19:31.720 --> 19:35.720
We run up to our room. We look at the man in the photo again.

19:35.720 --> 19:39.720
It is the man in black.

19:45.720 --> 19:49.720
Chapter 3. The train to Azwan.

19:49.720 --> 19:55.720
It is six o'clock in the morning. The sun is coming up.

19:55.720 --> 19:58.720
We are on the train to Azwan.

19:58.720 --> 20:04.720
Tyro is soon behind us. We are now in the country.

20:04.720 --> 20:10.720
I look out of the window. I see small houses and animals.

20:10.720 --> 20:14.720
Kate looks at the photo of the man in black.

20:14.720 --> 20:21.720
I have his bag and he has my bag, she says.

20:21.720 --> 20:26.720
What does he want your bag for? I ask her.

20:26.720 --> 20:32.720
I don't know, says Kate. I'm going to ask Mr. Johnson for his book.

20:32.720 --> 20:37.720
I want to find out about the hieroglyphs on the statue.

20:37.720 --> 20:42.720
She gets up and says, see you soon.

20:42.720 --> 20:48.720
I look at the people on the train. A mother and father are sitting with their children.

20:48.720 --> 20:54.720
The boy is eating breakfast. The girl is reading a book.

20:54.720 --> 21:00.720
A man in front of me is reading a newspaper. I look at the words on the front page.

21:00.720 --> 21:06.720
But I can't read them. The newspaper is in Arabic.

21:06.720 --> 21:12.720
And I can't read Arabic. Then I see a photo.

21:12.720 --> 21:16.720
It is a photo of the gold statue.

21:16.720 --> 21:24.720
Hello. I say to the man in front of me, do you speak English?

21:24.720 --> 21:26.720
He looks at me.

21:26.720 --> 21:32.720
Yes? He says. I do speak English.

21:32.720 --> 21:40.720
What does this story say, please? I ask him. He reads from the newspaper.

21:40.720 --> 21:48.720
Gold statue missing. A gold statue of Queen Nefertari is missing.

21:48.720 --> 21:53.720
Police are looking for a man in a black suit.

21:53.720 --> 22:02.720
Thank you. I say to the man. He smiles at me and reads his newspaper again.

22:02.720 --> 22:07.720
Kate sits down beside me. Her face is red.

22:07.720 --> 22:14.720
Maddy, she says. I know who the Egyptian queen is. She says.

22:14.720 --> 22:18.720
Mr. Johnson's book has a photo of the statue in it.

22:18.720 --> 22:27.720
I know who she is too. I say. Queen Nefertari, we say.

22:27.720 --> 22:34.720
It is six o'clock in the evening. The train stops at the station in Azwan.

22:34.720 --> 22:40.720
Kate is sleeping. It's a long journey from Cairo to Azwan.

22:40.720 --> 22:47.720
I open the window. The air is hot. I look up and down the station.

22:47.720 --> 22:55.720
People are getting off the train. Kate, we're here. I say. We're in Azwan.

22:55.720 --> 23:00.720
Kate opens her eyes. She looks out of the window too.

23:00.720 --> 23:06.720
Okay. Says Mr. Johnson. Get your bags and come with me.

23:06.720 --> 23:12.720
The hotel is near here. We're going to walk to it.

23:12.720 --> 23:17.720
We get off the train. We walk through the streets of Azwan.

23:17.720 --> 23:22.720
Lots of people are in the streets and in the shops.

23:22.720 --> 23:27.720
You can buy clothes and gold and silver in the shops.

23:27.720 --> 23:31.720
Says Mr. Johnson. And today is Market Day.

23:31.720 --> 23:38.720
The market has stalls with spices, rugs, food and coffee.

23:38.720 --> 23:45.720
The statue, Kate, I say to her. Are we going to tell Mr. Johnson?

23:45.720 --> 23:51.720
Yes, at the hotel, says Kate. We can tell him there.

23:51.720 --> 23:57.720
Okay. I say. We walk past the shops and stalls.

23:57.720 --> 24:03.720
I can smell the spices. I can smell coffee and food.

24:03.720 --> 24:10.720
I like the red and yellow rugs. Can we stop, please, Mr. Johnson?

24:10.720 --> 24:17.720
Says Peter Small. Paul Hand is taking photos of the things in the market.

24:18.720 --> 24:25.720
Mr. Johnson looks at us. Okay. He says and smiles.

24:25.720 --> 24:32.720
Kate and I look at a shop with clothes. We look at a stool with bags of spices.

24:32.720 --> 24:36.720
We go into a shop with silver and gold.

24:36.720 --> 24:44.720
Kate sees a small silver box. I see a gold necklace. I hold it in front of me.

24:44.720 --> 24:52.720
The necklace shines like the sun. It shines like the statue of the Egyptian queen.

24:52.720 --> 25:03.720
Then I see a man walk out of the shop. I can't see his face, but he is in a black suit. Is it him?

25:03.720 --> 25:13.720
I look for Kate. She is buying the silver box. She sees me and says, it's for my sister.

25:14.720 --> 25:23.720
Kate, where's the bag? I say. Where's the statue? It's here, she says.

25:23.720 --> 25:35.720
Kate looks at the ground. The bag isn't there. Oh no, she says. Her face is white. Where is it?

25:36.720 --> 25:51.720
Chapter 4. A good story. We're in the hotel. Mr. Johnson is looking at us.

25:51.720 --> 26:01.720
Your bag is missing. He says to Kate. Yes, she says. But it's not my bag.

26:01.720 --> 26:06.720
And this bag has a missing statue in it?

26:06.720 --> 26:15.720
Says Mr. Johnson. Yes, we say. And the police are looking for this man, says Kate.

26:15.720 --> 26:27.720
She gives Mr. Johnson the photo of the man in black. Look, do you see? He's taking my bag and he's putting his bag in its place.

26:28.720 --> 26:36.720
What? Says Mr. Johnson. He gives you his bag with a statue in it.

26:36.720 --> 26:48.720
Yes, he's hiding the statue, I say. The police aren't going to look for the statue in a school girl's bag, says Kate.

26:48.720 --> 26:55.720
It's a good place to hide a statue. And where is this statue now?

26:55.720 --> 27:04.720
Says Mr. Johnson. He has it again, says Kate. He's here in us one too.

27:04.720 --> 27:14.720
Mr. Johnson doesn't speak. Then he smiles. It's a good story, girls. He says.

27:15.720 --> 27:26.720
The gold statue of an Egyptian queen, a man in black, the police. It's a good detective story.

27:26.720 --> 27:37.720
Mr. Johnson, please, says Kate. But Mr. Johnson walks to the door. He opens it and smiles again.

27:37.720 --> 27:46.720
We are going to go to Abu Simbal tomorrow. We are going to see the temple of Ramesses the Great.

27:46.720 --> 27:57.720
We are going to see the temple of his queen, Nefertari. It's going to be a long, hot day, girls. Good night.

27:58.720 --> 28:12.720
I look at Kate and say, a good detective story. But this isn't a story. It isn't, says Kate.

28:12.720 --> 28:23.720
We are on the bus to Abu Simbal. I open the window. The air is hot on my face. I look in front of me.

28:23.720 --> 28:34.720
I look at the sand of the Sahara Desert. I see blue sky and yellow sand. It's a big desert.

28:34.720 --> 28:47.720
Soon we are at Abu Simbal. We see the blue waters of Lake Nasa. The temples of Ramesses the Great and Queen Nefertari are in front of us.

28:47.720 --> 28:53.720
Big statues of Ramesses the Great sit at the front of his temple.

28:53.720 --> 29:02.720
Wow, says Kate. Look at the statues of Ramesses the Great. They are big.

29:02.720 --> 29:12.720
Poor hand jumps off the bus. He takes photos of Lake Nasa. He takes photos of the big statues.

29:12.720 --> 29:24.720
We walk into the temple of Ramesses the Great. Kate speaks to Mr. Johnson. She asks him a question about Ramesses the Great.

29:24.720 --> 29:38.720
I look at the statues in the temple. Then I see him, the man in black. He is standing beside one of the statues.

29:38.720 --> 29:50.720
He is speaking to a man with white hair. The brown bag is on the ground between them. Is the statue in the bag?

29:50.720 --> 30:03.720
I look for Kate. She is speaking to poor hand. He is taking her photo beside a statue. She is small beside the statue.

30:03.720 --> 30:18.720
The man in black walks outside. I walk outside too. He goes into the temple of Queen Nefertari. I go in too. The temple is small.

30:18.720 --> 30:27.720
The ground is dirty. The air is hot. I can't see him. Where is he?

30:27.720 --> 30:41.720
Then a hand is over my mouth. Don't speak, girl. Says a voice behind me.

30:42.720 --> 31:01.720
Chapter 5, Finding Queen Nefertari. My face is hot. I am afraid. Don't say a word. Says the voice. It is a man's voice. You see this?

31:01.720 --> 31:11.720
He has a knife. He takes his hand away from my mouth. I see his face. It is the man in black.

31:11.720 --> 31:20.720
I come to Abu Simba and you are here too. He says, what are you doing here?

31:20.720 --> 31:37.720
I am looking at the temple. Where is your friend? He asks. I don't know. I say, what are you doing here? Where is the statue?

31:37.720 --> 31:57.720
He smiles. It is in the bag. He says, what are you going to do with it? I ask. I am going to sell it. He says, the man takes the statue out of the bag.

31:57.720 --> 32:12.720
He looks at it and laughs. Nefertari's temple is a good place to sell Nefertari's statue. It is a long way from Cairo. It is a long way for the police.

32:13.720 --> 32:34.720
He puts the statue in the bag. A man is here to come here soon. He is going to give me a lot. I can get a lot of things with that money. New clothes, fast cars. I like new clothes and fast cars.

32:34.720 --> 32:49.720
He laughs again. I see his yellow teeth. I don't like this man. His eyes are black. His hands are dirty. He is a bad man.

32:49.720 --> 33:04.720
But the question is, what do I do with you? He asks. I look at the ground. I look at the bag on the ground. He looks at me again.

33:05.720 --> 33:27.720
I am going to tie you up. He says, I am going to tie you up with this rope. He takes a rope from the bag. Then I am going to go to Spain. I like the food in Spain. Now, get over there.

33:28.720 --> 33:52.720
He pushes me. I fall to the ground. My face is in the sand. I pick up sand in my hands. Get up. He says, get up now. I stand up. He comes near me. I throw the sand at his face. I throw it into his eyes.

33:52.720 --> 34:10.720
The knife and the rope fall to the ground. He puts his hands to his eyes. He can't see. He shouts. I pick up the bag. I run to the front of the temple.

34:11.720 --> 34:35.720
Help. I shout. Help me. A man is standing in front of me. I can't see his face. Is it the bad man's friend? I run into the man. He falls to the ground. It's Mr. Johnson. And Kate is behind him.

34:35.720 --> 34:43.720
It's OK, Maddie. He says, it's OK. The police are here.

34:45.720 --> 34:56.720
Kate and I are in our English class. Mr. Johnson is reading our stories about Egypt. He stands up in front of the class.

34:57.720 --> 35:07.720
You are good writers. He says, I like your stories. But only one story can be the winner.

35:08.720 --> 35:24.720
He looks at us. And the winner is? He looks at us again. Land of gold by Kate Wilkinson. It's a very good detective story, Kate.

35:26.720 --> 35:37.720
We smile at Kate. She smiles too. Thank you. She says, where are we going to go next, Mr. Johnson?

35:37.720 --> 35:52.720
We're going to go to Russia next year. He says, oh good. Says Kate. I'm reading a book on Russia. The old buildings there have gold statues.

35:52.720 --> 35:55.720
Mr. Johnson smiles.

